01:00:56,600 --> 01:00:59,120
Notre Dame's first bigbreak 
 of the game.

1924
01:00:59,240 --> 01:01:02,880
I came here because there's 
 gonna be more bloodshed.

1925
01:01:02,960 --> 01:01:05,200
I want you to know about it 
 before it happens...

1926
01:01:05,320 --> 01:01:07,680
so that there's no danger 
 of starting another war.

1927
01:01:07,760 --> 01:01:10,680
Nobody wants another war.

1928
01:01:10,800 --> 01:01:14,320
Frank Pentangeli came to my home 
 and he asked my permission...

1929
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:15,880
to get rid of the Rosato brothers.

1930
01:01:15,960 --> 01:01:18,200
When I refused, 
 he tried to have me killed.

1931
01:01:18,320 --> 01:01:21,640
He was stupid. I was lucky. 
 I'll visit him soon.

1932
01:01:21,760 --> 01:01:24,920
The important thing is that 
 nothing interfere...

1933
01:01:25,040 --> 01:01:26,840
with our plans for the future.

1934
01:01:26,960 --> 01:01:30,480
- Yours and mine. 
 - Nothing is more important.

1935
01:01:30,600 --> 01:01:32,040
Good.

1936
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:34,920
You're a wise 
 and considerate young man.

1937
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:37,760
And you're a great man, 
 Mr. Roth.

1938
01:01:37,840 --> 01:01:41,720
- There's much I can learn from you. 
 - What can I do to help, Michael?

1939
01:01:41,840 --> 01:01:44,560
To the 32, and is downed there 
 by Danny Zika.

1940
