01:14:29,040 --> 01:14:30,640
Cuba! Cuba!

2089
01:15:10,120 --> 01:15:12,920
Most respected gentlemen...

2090
01:15:13,040 --> 01:15:15,120
allow me to welcome you 
 to the city of Havana.

2091
01:15:17,160 --> 01:15:21,960
I want to thank this distinguished 
 group of American industrialists...

2092
01:15:23,920 --> 01:15:25,720
for continuing to work 
 with Cuba...

2093
01:15:27,440 --> 01:15:29,520
toward the greatest period 
 of prosperity...

2094
01:15:31,120 --> 01:15:32,920
in her entire history.

2095
01:15:34,360 --> 01:15:38,200
Mr. William Shaw, representing 
 the General Fruit Company;

2096
01:15:40,040 --> 01:15:41,840
Misters Corngold and Dant...

2097
01:15:41,920 --> 01:15:44,600
of United Telephone 
 and Telegraph Company;

2098
01:15:46,800 --> 01:15:48,960
Mr. Petty, 
 regional vice president...

2099
01:15:49,080 --> 01:15:51,360
of the Pan American 
 Mining Corporation;

2100
01:15:53,960 --> 01:15:56,080
Mr. Robert Allen 
 of South American Sugar;,

2101
01:15:58,320 --> 01:16:00,360
Mr. Michael Corleone of Nevada...

2102
01:16:02,160 --> 01:16:05,320
representing our associates in 
 tourism and leisure activities;

2103
01:16:06,800 --> 01:16:09,560
and my old friend and associate 
 from Florida...

2104
01:16:11,640 --> 01:16:13,680
Mr. Hyman Roth.

2105
01:16:13,800 --> 01:16:15,480
I would like to take this 
 opportunity...

2106
01:16:15,600 --> 01:16:17,400
to thank United 
 Telephone and Telegraph...

2107
01:16:17,480 --> 01:16:19,320
for their lovely Christmas gift:

2108
01:16:23,760 --> 01:16:25,560
a solid gold telephone.

2109
01:16:28,200 --> 01:16:31,000
Perhaps you gentlemen would 
 like to take a look at it.

2110
01:16:32,440 --> 01:16:34,080
- Mr. President. 
 - Yes?

2111
01:16:34,200 --> 01:16:37,120
Perhaps you would discuss 
 the status of rebel activity...

2112
01:16:37,240 --> 01:16:39,840
and what this can mean 
 to our businesses.

2113
01:16:39,960 --> 01:16:41,360
- Of course. 
 - Very lovely.

2114
01:16:41,440 --> 01:16:43,800
I want to assure you 
 that although the rebels...

2115
01:16:43,920 --> 01:16:46,960
have mounted an impressive 
 campaign in Las Villas...

2116
01:16:52,960 --> 01:16:55,160
my staff indicates 
 with assurance...

2117
01:16:55,280 --> 01:16:59,960
we'll drive them out of the city 
 of Santa Clara before the new year.

2118
01:17:02,480 --> 01:17:04,920
And I want to put you all 
 at ease.

2119
01:17:05,040 --> 01:17:08,760
We will tolerate no guerillas 
 in the casinos or swimming pools.

2120
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:28,720
He say that they are 
 making arrest...

2121
01:17:28,800 --> 01:17:31,600
and in a few minutes 
 he'll let us through.

2122
01:17:32,120 --> 01:17:34,080
Johnny.

2123
01:17:55,680 --> 01:17:58,680
Well, I hope my age 
 is correct.

2124
01:17:58,800 --> 01:18:01,760
I'm always accurate 
 about my age.

2125
01:18:01,880 --> 01:18:05,280
Make sure that everybody 
 sees the cake before we cut it.

2126
01:18:08,960 --> 01:18:11,560
I'm very pleased...

2127
01:18:11,640 --> 01:18:14,440
you were all able to come 
 from such distances...

2128
01:18:14,520 --> 01:18:15,680
to be with me today.

2129
01:18:17,560 --> 01:18:20,120
When a man comes 
 to this point in his life...

2130
01:18:21,600 --> 01:18:24,920
he wants to turn over the 
 things he's been blessed with--

2131
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:26,920
turn them over to friends--

2132
01:18:27,000 --> 01:18:31,080
as a reward 
 for the friends he's had...

2133
01:18:31,160 --> 01:18:36,200
and to make sure that everything 
 goes well after he's gone.

2134
01:18:36,280 --> 01:18:38,840
- Not for years. 
 - Hear, hear.

2135
01:18:38,960 --> 01:18:42,640
The doctors would disagree, 
 but what do they know?

2136
01:18:44,080 --> 01:18:48,880
These are wonderful things 
 that we've achieved in Havana...

2137
01:18:49,000 --> 01:18:51,920
and there's no limit to 
 where we can go from here.

2138
01:18:52,040 --> 01:18:56,600
This kind of government knows how 
 to help business, to encourage it.

2139
01:18:56,720 --> 01:19:00,560
The hotels here 
 are bigger and swankier...

2140
01:19:00,680 --> 01:19:03,200
than any of the rough joints 
 we've put in in Vegas.

2141
01:19:03,320 --> 01:19:06,520
And we can thank our friends 
 in the Cuban government...

2142
01:19:06,600 --> 01:19:09,480
which has put up half of the cash, 
 with the Teamsters...

2143
01:19:09,560 --> 01:19:11,040
on a dollar-for-dollar basis;

2144
01:19:11,160 --> 01:19:13,880
has relaxed restrictions 
 on imports.

2145
01:19:13,960 --> 01:19:18,200
What I'm saying is that we have now 
 what we have always needed:

2146
01:19:18,280 --> 01:19:20,920
real partnership 
 with a government.

2147
01:19:21,040 --> 01:19:23,520
Smaller piece.

2148
01:19:23,640 --> 01:19:26,080
You all know Michael Corleone...

2149
01:19:26,200 --> 01:19:28,320
and we all remember his father.

2150
01:19:28,440 --> 01:19:31,920
At the time of my retirement 
 or death...

2151
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:36,280
I turn over all my interest 
 in the Havana operation...

2152
01:19:36,400 --> 01:19:37,560
to his control.

2153
01:19:37,680 --> 01:19:41,560
But all of you will share.

2154
01:19:41,680 --> 01:19:45,200
The Nacionale will go to 
 the Lakeville Road boys.

2155
01:19:45,320 --> 01:19:50,960
The Capri to the Corleone family. 
 The Sevilla Biltmore also.

2156
01:19:51,040 --> 01:19:54,760
But Eddie Levine of Newport will 
 bring in the Pennino brothers...

2157
01:19:54,840 --> 01:19:56,560
Dino and Eddie, for a piece...

2158
01:19:56,640 --> 01:19:59,360
and also to handle 
 the actual casino operations.

2159
01:19:59,480 --> 01:20:02,840
And we've saved a piece for 
 some friends in Nevada...

2160
01:20:02,960 --> 01:20:06,480
to make sure that things 
 go smooth back home.

2161
01:20:06,560 --> 01:20:11,320
I want all of you 
 to enjoy your cake...

2162
01:20:11,440 --> 01:20:13,240
so enjoy.

2163
01:20:13,360 --> 01:20:15,160
- Happy birthday. 
 - Happy birthday.

2164
01:20:16,920 --> 01:20:20,720
I saw an interesting thing 
 happen today.

2165
01:20:20,840 --> 01:20:23,840
A rebel was being arrested 
 by the military police...

2166
01:20:23,960 --> 01:20:25,640
and rather than be taken alive...

2167
01:20:25,720 --> 01:20:28,240
he exploded a grenade he had 
 hidden in his jacket.

2168
01:20:28,360 --> 01:20:31,640
He killed himself, and he took 
 a captain of the command with him.

2169
01:20:31,720 --> 01:20:33,840
- Right, Johnny? 
 - Those rebels, they're lunatics.

2170
01:20:33,920 --> 01:20:37,040
- Yes, I agree. 
 - Maybe so.

2171
01:20:37,160 --> 01:20:38,680
But it occurred to me...

2172
01:20:38,800 --> 01:20:42,000
the soldiers are paid to fight, 
 the rebels aren't.

2173
01:20:42,080 --> 01:20:44,160
What does that tell you?

2174
01:20:44,280 --> 01:20:46,080
They could win.

2175
01:20:47,840 --> 01:20:50,520
This country has had rebels 
 for the last 50 years.

2176
01:20:50,640 --> 01:20:55,080
It's in their blood. I've been 
 coming here since the '20s.

2177
01:20:55,160 --> 01:20:58,840
We were running molasses out 
 of Havana when you were a baby...

2178
01:20:58,960 --> 01:21:02,400
the trucks owned by your father.

2179
01:21:02,520 --> 01:21:04,880
Michael.

2180
01:21:10,720 --> 01:21:13,520
I'd rather we talked about 
 this when we we're alone.

2181
01:21:16,320 --> 01:21:19,120
The two million 
 never got to the island.

2182
01:21:24,720 --> 01:21:27,720
I wouldn't want it to get around 
 that you held back the money...

2183
01:21:27,800 --> 01:21:31,040
because you had second thoughts 
 about the rebels.

2184
01:21:36,200 --> 01:21:39,000
Ah, sit down, Michael.

2185
01:21:39,120 --> 01:21:40,920
Sit down.

2186
01:21:47,160 --> 01:21:50,840
If I could only live to see it, 
 to be there with you.

2187
01:21:50,920 --> 01:21:53,160
Ohh.

2188
01:21:53,240 --> 01:21:55,640
What I wouldn't give for...

2189
01:21:55,720 --> 01:21:57,560
20 more years.

2190
01:21:59,040 --> 01:22:01,480
Here we are, protected--

2191
01:22:01,560 --> 01:22:03,560
free to make our profiits without 
 Kefauver...

2192
01:22:03,640 --> 01:22:07,200
the goddamn Justice 
 Department and the FBl--

2193
01:22:07,320 --> 01:22:10,680
90 miles away, partnership 
 with a friendly government.

2194
01:22:12,080 --> 01:22:16,080
Ninety miles. It's nothing.

2195
01:22:16,200 --> 01:22:18,640
Just one small step, 
 looking for a man...

2196
01:22:18,760 --> 01:22:21,800
that wants to be President 
 of the United States...

2197
01:22:21,880 --> 01:22:25,120
and having the cash 
 to make it possible.

2198
01:22:25,240 --> 01:22:27,040
Michael...

2199
01:22:28,600 --> 01:22:31,320
we're bigger than U.S.Steel.

2200
01:22:56,440 --> 01:22:58,720
Mikey, how are ya? Okay?

2201
01:23:00,680 --> 01:23:03,280
Hiya. Freddie Corleone.

2202
01:23:06,360 --> 01:23:08,560
Jesus Christ, what a trip.

2203
01:23:08,640 --> 01:23:10,040
The whole time I'm thinkin'...

2204
01:23:10,120 --> 01:23:12,120
"What if somebody knows 
 what I got in here?"

2205
01:23:12,240 --> 01:23:16,400
Imagine that. Two million dollars 
 on the seat next to me.

2206
01:23:16,480 --> 01:23:18,320
All right.

2207
01:23:19,800 --> 01:23:22,120
- Whoops. Excuse me. 
 - No, it's okay.

2208
01:23:24,320 --> 01:23:26,160
You wanna count it?

2209
01:23:30,400 --> 01:23:33,720
Mikey, what the hell's 
 goin' on anyway?

2210
01:23:33,840 --> 01:23:35,960
The family's making 
 an investment in Havana.

2211
01:23:36,080 --> 01:23:39,280
- This is a gift for the president. 
 - Oh.

2212
01:23:39,360 --> 01:23:41,240
Well, that's great.

2213
01:23:41,360 --> 01:23:43,160
Havana's great.

2214
01:23:44,240 --> 01:23:46,040
It's my kind of town.

2215
01:23:47,520 --> 01:23:49,520
- Anybody I know in Havana? 
 - I don't know.

2216
01:23:49,640 --> 01:23:51,520
Hyman Roth? Johnny Ola?

2217
01:23:54,840 --> 01:23:57,280
No. I never met them.

2218
01:24:00,920 --> 01:24:03,120
Listen, Mikey...

2219
01:24:03,200 --> 01:24:05,040
I'm kind of, uh--

2220
01:24:08,440 --> 01:24:09,760
kind of nervous from the trip.

2221
01:24:09,880 --> 01:24:13,360
Uh, can I-- can I get 
 a, uh, drink or somethin'?

2222
01:24:13,440 --> 01:24:16,560
I thought maybe we'd-- 
 we'd go out together.

2223
01:24:16,680 --> 01:24:19,480
I know a place we can spend 
 some time together. Okay?

2224
01:24:21,880 --> 01:24:24,880
Sometimes I think I should've 
 married a woman like you did...

2225
01:24:25,000 --> 01:24:27,320
Like Kay.

2226
01:24:27,400 --> 01:24:29,720
Have kids, have a family.

2227
01:24:32,280 --> 01:24:35,520
For once in my life 
 be more like...

2228
01:24:36,880 --> 01:24:38,400
Pop.

2229
01:24:40,560 --> 01:24:45,120
It's not easy to be a son, 
 Fredo. It's not easy.

2230
01:24:45,240 --> 01:24:48,240
Mama used to tease me. She'd say, 
 "You don't belong to me.

2231
01:24:48,320 --> 01:24:51,720
You were left on the doorstep 
 by gypsies."

2232
01:24:51,800 --> 01:24:54,560
Sometimes I think it's true.

2233
01:24:54,680 --> 01:24:56,480
You're no gypsy, Fredo.

2234
01:24:58,040 --> 01:24:59,960
Mikey, I--

2235
01:25:00,080 --> 01:25:01,880
I was mad at you.

2236
01:25:08,840 --> 01:25:12,600
Why didn't we spend time 
 like this before?

2237
01:25:12,720 --> 01:25:15,000
You want a drink, right? 
 Waiter.

2238
01:25:22,520 --> 01:25:25,240
- How do you say banana daiquiri? 
 - Banana daiquiri.

2239
01:25:25,360 --> 01:25:27,520
- That's it? 
 - That's it.

2240
01:25:27,640 --> 01:25:30,400
- Uh, uno banana daiquiri. 
 - Banana daiquiri. Si, senor.

2241
01:25:30,520 --> 01:25:32,800
And, uh, a club soda.

2242
01:25:40,320 --> 01:25:43,000
Senator Geary's flying in 
 from Washington tomorrow night...

2243
01:25:43,120 --> 01:25:45,400
with some people, 
 some government people...

2244
01:25:45,520 --> 01:25:48,560
and I want you to show 'em 
 a good time in Havana.

2245
01:25:50,800 --> 01:25:53,120
It's my specialty, right?

2246
01:25:53,240 --> 01:25:56,240
- Can I trust you with something? 
 - Ofcourse, Mike.

2247
01:25:59,880 --> 01:26:03,120
In the evening, we're all invited 
 to the presidential palace...

2248
01:26:03,200 --> 01:26:05,680
a reception to bring in 
 the new year.

2249
01:26:05,760 --> 01:26:07,600
After it's over...

2250
01:26:07,680 --> 01:26:10,120
they're gonna take me home 
 in a military car...

2251
01:26:10,200 --> 01:26:13,760
alone, for my protection...

2252
01:26:13,880 --> 01:26:17,120
and before I reach my hotel 
 I'll be assassinated.

2253
01:26:34,720 --> 01:26:37,680
- Who? 
 - Roth.

2254
01:26:43,240 --> 01:26:46,040
It was Roth who tried 
 to kill me in my home.

2255
01:26:47,760 --> 01:26:49,720
It was Roth all along.

2256
01:26:49,840 --> 01:26:54,840
He acts like I'm his son, 
 his successor...

2257
01:26:54,960 --> 01:26:57,760
but he thinks he's gonna live 
 forever and he wants me out.

2258
01:27:02,680 --> 01:27:03,720
How can I help?

2259
01:27:03,800 --> 01:27:07,040
You just go along 
 as though you know nothing.

2260
01:27:07,160 --> 01:27:10,920
- I've already made my move. 
 - What move?

2261
01:27:11,000 --> 01:27:13,400
Hyman Roth'll never see 
 the new year.

2262
01:27:30,040 --> 01:27:32,520
He says you have to take it easy 
 and he'll give you a prescription.

2263
01:27:32,600 --> 01:27:33,840
He'll be back tomorrow.

2264
01:27:33,920 --> 01:27:36,280
I want my own doctor. 
 Fly him in from Miami.

2265
01:27:36,360 --> 01:27:38,480
I don't trust a doctor 
 can't speak English.

2266
01:27:44,600 --> 01:27:46,400
Honey, go down to the casino.

2267
01:27:46,520 --> 01:27:49,760
- If you're sure you're better. 
 - Feel fine.

2268
01:27:51,640 --> 01:27:54,320
- Play the bingo game. 
 - Nice to see you, Mr. Paul.

2269
01:27:54,400 --> 01:27:56,280
-Just make yourself at home. 
 - Thank you.

2270
01:27:58,080 --> 01:27:59,440
My sixth sense tells me...

2271
01:27:59,520 --> 01:28:01,960
your brother Fredo brought 
 a bag full of money.

2272
01:28:02,040 --> 01:28:05,080
Where is it?

2273
01:28:05,200 --> 01:28:07,520
You're pulling out?

2274
01:28:07,640 --> 01:28:11,360
Just wanna-- 
 I just wanna wait.

2275
01:28:14,600 --> 01:28:17,080
How do you feel?

2276
01:28:17,200 --> 01:28:19,280
Terrible. I'd give four million...

2277
01:28:19,400 --> 01:28:22,480
just to be able to take a piss 
 without it hurting.

2278
01:28:22,600 --> 01:28:25,760
Who had Frank Pentangeli killed?

2279
01:28:25,880 --> 01:28:28,120
The Rosato brothers.

2280
01:28:28,240 --> 01:28:31,640
I know. But who gave 
 the go-ahead?

2281
01:28:31,760 --> 01:28:34,520
I know I didn't.

2282
01:28:41,440 --> 01:28:43,880
There was this kid 
 I grew up with.

2283
01:28:43,960 --> 01:28:46,040
He was younger than me.

2284
01:28:46,160 --> 01:28:48,560
Sort of looked up to me, 
 you know.

2285
01:28:48,640 --> 01:28:52,080
We did our first work together.

2286
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:54,160
Worked our way 
 out of the street.

2287
01:28:54,240 --> 01:28:56,160
Things were good. 
 We made the most of it.

2288
01:28:57,440 --> 01:28:59,840
During Prohibition...

2289
01:28:59,960 --> 01:29:01,840
we ran molasses into Canada.

2290
01:29:01,920 --> 01:29:04,280
Made a fortune. Your father too.

2291
01:29:06,720 --> 01:29:09,640
As much as anyone...

2292
01:29:09,720 --> 01:29:12,160
I loved him and trusted him.

2293
01:29:15,080 --> 01:29:18,400
Later on he had an idea...

2294
01:29:18,520 --> 01:29:20,560
to build a city...

2295
01:29:20,680 --> 01:29:24,240
out of a desert stopover for G.I. s 
 on their way to the West Coast.

2296
01:29:26,200 --> 01:29:29,760
That kid's name was Moe Green...

2297
01:29:29,880 --> 01:29:32,960
and the city he invented 
 was Las Vegas.

2298
01:29:34,640 --> 01:29:36,960
This was a great man...

2299
01:29:37,080 --> 01:29:39,440
a man of vision and guts...

2300
01:29:39,560 --> 01:29:44,520
and there isn't even a plaque 
 or a signpost or a statue of him...

2301
01:29:44,600 --> 01:29:47,400
in that town.

2302
01:29:47,480 --> 01:29:50,800
Someone put a bullet 
 through his eye.

2303
01:29:52,120 --> 01:29:55,240
No one knows 
 who gave the order.

2304
01:29:55,320 --> 01:29:58,320
When I heard it I wasn't angry.

2305
01:29:58,440 --> 01:30:00,400
I knew Moe; 
 I knew he was headstrong.

2306
01:30:00,480 --> 01:30:04,240
Talking loud, 
 saying stupid things.

2307
01:30:04,320 --> 01:30:07,440
So when he turned up dead...

2308
01:30:07,520 --> 01:30:10,600
I let it go...

2309
01:30:10,680 --> 01:30:13,800
and I said to myself...

2310
01:30:13,880 --> 01:30:17,640
"This is the business 
 we've chosen."

2311
01:30:17,720 --> 01:30:20,400
I didn't ask...

2312
01:30:20,520 --> 01:30:22,360
who gave the order...

2313
01:30:22,440 --> 01:30:25,240
because it had nothing 
 to do with business.

2314
01:30:33,560 --> 01:30:37,280
That two million 
 in a bag in your room--

2315
01:30:40,120 --> 01:30:41,920
I'm going in...

2316
01:30:42,040 --> 01:30:44,000
to take a nap.

2317
01:30:44,120 --> 01:30:46,120
When I wake...

2318
01:30:46,200 --> 01:30:49,720
if the money's on the table 
 I'll know I have a partner.

2319
01:30:49,840 --> 01:30:52,120
If it isn't, 
 I'll know I don't.

2320
01:31:45,560 --> 01:31:47,600
All right, does everybody 
 know everybody here, huh?

2321
01:31:47,680 --> 01:31:49,560
- This is Senator Geary. 
 - How are you, Senator?

2322
01:31:49,680 --> 01:31:52,760
Good to see you, Mike. I'm glad 
 we could spend time together.

2323
01:31:52,880 --> 01:31:55,800
- Senator Payton from Florida. 
 - How you doing, Mike?

2324
01:31:55,920 --> 01:31:58,240
- And Judge DeMalco from New York. 
 - How do you do, sir?

2325
01:31:58,360 --> 01:32:00,400
- Fine, thank you. 
 - Senator Ream from Maryland.

2326
01:32:00,520 --> 01:32:03,680
- I've been looking forward to this. 
 - This is Fred Corngold from U.T.T.

2327
01:32:03,800 --> 01:32:07,120
- I know Fred. How are you? 
 - Fred does a mean cha-cha-cha.

2328
01:32:07,240 --> 01:32:10,560
- Oh, he does, huh? 
 - Gentlemen, it's refiill time.

2329
01:32:10,680 --> 01:32:15,000
Try some of them local drinks-- 
 uh, cuba libre, pina colada.

2330
01:32:15,120 --> 01:32:18,840
I think I'll try one of 
 those redheaded Yolandas.

2331
01:32:18,920 --> 01:32:22,680
- That you got. Congusto. 
 - Johnny.

2332
01:32:22,800 --> 01:32:26,280
You don't know my brother Fredo, 
 do you, Johnny? Johnny Ola, Fredo.

2333
01:32:26,360 --> 01:32:28,440
- We never met. Johnny Ola. 
 - Pleasure.

2334
01:32:31,000 --> 01:32:33,200
Gentlemen, to a night in Havana.

2335
01:32:33,320 --> 01:32:35,160
- Happy New Year. 
 - Happy New Year.

2336
01:32:36,440 --> 01:32:38,960
- Happy New Year. 
 - That's right, huh?

2337
01:32:42,960 --> 01:32:46,160
- Checkin' in now. Right now. 
 - Never fear! Pat Geary's here!

2338
01:32:46,240 --> 01:32:48,960
- Hey, Fred. 
 - Cheers! Hey!

2339
01:32:49,080 --> 01:32:51,440
- Hey, Freddie, why are we standin'? 
 - Come on, man!

2340
01:32:51,560 --> 01:32:54,200
Everybody stands, 
 but it's worth it.

2341
01:32:54,320 --> 01:32:57,000
- You're not gonna believe this. 
 - I don't believe it already.

2342
01:32:57,080 --> 01:33:00,480
- That's right. Fifty dollars. 
 - You got a bet, mister.

2343
01:33:08,600 --> 01:33:10,960
That's him. That's Superman.

2344
01:33:42,280 --> 01:33:44,760
- Jesus Christ! 
 - Did I tell ya, or did I tell ya?

2345
01:33:46,480 --> 01:33:48,920
- I don't believe it. 
 - That thing's gotta be a fake.

2346
01:33:49,040 --> 01:33:52,760
That ain't no fake. That's real. 
 That's why they call him Superman.

2347
01:33:52,880 --> 01:33:56,720
Hey, Freddie. Freddie. 
 Where did you find this place?

2348
01:33:56,800 --> 01:33:59,080
Johnny Ola told me about 
 this place. He brought me here.

2349
01:33:59,160 --> 01:34:01,000
I didn't believe it, 
 but seein' is believin', huh?

2350
01:34:01,080 --> 01:34:04,400
- I see it and I don't believe it. 
 - Fifty bucks, Pat.

2351
01:34:04,520 --> 01:34:06,000
Old man Roth'd never come here...

2352
01:34:06,120 --> 01:34:08,880
but ol'Johnny knows these places 
 like the back of his hand.

2353
01:34:08,960 --> 01:34:11,440
Now watch him. He's gonna 
 break the cracker with it.

2354
01:34:11,560 --> 01:34:14,680
I wanna see him break a brick.

2355
01:34:14,800 --> 01:34:17,080
He could knock down a building.

2356
01:35:32,280 --> 01:35:35,360
Relax, Senor Roth. We're 
 taking you to the hospital.

2357
01:36:17,480 --> 01:36:19,760
And in my judgment 
 you'll continue to get those...

2358
01:36:19,880 --> 01:36:22,600
because I don't believe 
 that President Eisenhower...

2359
01:36:22,720 --> 01:36:24,120
will ever pull out of Cuba.

2360
01:36:24,200 --> 01:36:27,760
Not as long as we have over one billion 
 dollars invested in this country.

2361
01:36:30,880 --> 01:36:34,280
Now, the American public 
 believes in nonintervention.

2362
01:36:34,400 --> 01:36:37,160
Fredo. Where you goin'?

2363
01:36:37,280 --> 01:36:40,320
I'm gonna get me a real drink, 
 'cause I can't--

2364
01:37:34,080 --> 01:37:37,400
What kept Mr. Roth? 
 I understood he was coming.

2365
01:37:37,480 --> 01:37:40,880
Ream, what's the protocol? How long 
 should we stay around here?

2366
01:37:41,000 --> 01:37:43,760
Oh, I don't know. I think 
 a half hour oughta do it.

2367
01:37:43,880 --> 01:37:46,240
Just long enough 
 to bring in the new year.

2368
01:39:16,880 --> 01:39:20,720
There's a plane waiting for us 
 to take us to Miami in an hour.

2369
01:39:20,840 --> 01:39:23,120
Don't make a big thing about it.

2370
01:39:27,040 --> 01:39:29,320
I know it was you, Fredo.

2371
01:39:29,440 --> 01:39:32,120
You broke my heart.

2372
01:39:32,200 --> 01:39:35,120
You broke my heart.

2373
01:41:12,160 --> 01:41:15,360
Fredo! Come on.

2374
01:41:15,480 --> 01:41:18,640
Come with me. It's the only 
 way out of here tonight.

2375
01:41:18,760 --> 01:41:21,240
Roth is dead. Fredo.

2376
01:41:21,320 --> 01:41:24,160
Fredo, come with me! 
 You're still my brother!

2377
01:41:24,240 --> 01:41:26,960
Fredo! Fredo!

2378
01:41:45,200 --> 01:41:46,960
U.S. passports only.

2379
01:41:49,600 --> 01:41:54,160
- U.S. passports only. 
 - I'm from the United States Senate.

2380
01:41:56,720 --> 01:41:58,960
- Back, please. 
 - Please! I must leave!

2381
01:43:04,560 --> 01:43:07,520
Al, get me a wet towel.

2382
01:43:14,280 --> 01:43:16,080
Kay know I'm back?

2383
01:43:20,680 --> 01:43:23,840
What about my boy? Did you get 
 him something for Christmas?

2384
01:43:23,960 --> 01:43:27,320
- I took care of it. 
 - What was it so I'll know?

2385
01:43:27,400 --> 01:43:30,720
It was a little car with an electric 
 motor that he could ride in.

2386
01:43:30,840 --> 01:43:32,680
It was nice.

2387
01:43:34,800 --> 01:43:37,520
Thank you, Al.

2388
01:43:37,640 --> 01:43:39,960
Fellas, could you step outside 
 for a minute, please?

2389
01:43:57,360 --> 01:43:59,200
Where's my brother?

2390
01:43:59,280 --> 01:44:03,080
Uh, Roth got out on a private boat. 
 He's in a hospital in Miami.

2391
01:44:03,160 --> 01:44:05,960
He had a stroke. 
 He recovered okay.

2392
01:44:06,080 --> 01:44:10,400
- Your bodyguard's dead. 
 - I asked about Fredo.

2393
01:44:10,480 --> 01:44:13,320
I think he got out. He must be 
 somewhere in New York.

2394
01:44:16,600 --> 01:44:19,000
All right.

2395
01:44:19,080 --> 01:44:21,880
I want you to get 
 in touch with him.

2396
01:44:21,960 --> 01:44:24,880
I know he's scared. 
 Tell him everything's all right.

2397
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:26,560
Tell him I know Roth misled him;

2398
01:44:26,680 --> 01:44:29,160
that he didn't know 
 they were gonna try to kill me.

2399
01:44:31,000 --> 01:44:33,160
And they can come in now.

2400
01:44:33,280 --> 01:44:35,840
Oh, there was something else.

2401
01:44:35,960 --> 01:44:38,480
What?

2402
01:44:43,280 --> 01:44:45,160
What? 
 Come on. What?

2403
01:44:47,560 --> 01:44:49,600
Kay had a miscarriage. 
 She lost the baby.

2404
01:45:02,080 --> 01:45:04,360
- Was it a boy? 
 - After three and a half months--

2405
01:45:04,480 --> 01:45:08,560
Can't you give me a straight answer 
 anymore? Was it a boy?

2406
01:45:11,120 --> 01:45:12,960
I really don't know.

2407
01:49:32,400 --> 01:49:33,320
I take care of everything.

2408
01:51:11,200 --> 01:51:13,080
Vito, here's my $50.

2409
01:51:31,400 --> 01:51:35,200
I'll make an offer he don't refuse. 
 Don't worry.

2410
02:03:42,960 --> 02:03:45,720
From the year 1942 
 to the present time...

2411
02:03:45,800 --> 02:03:49,280
you were an employee 
 of the Genco Olive Oil Company?

2412
02:03:49,360 --> 02:03:50,880
That's right.

2413
02:03:51,920 --> 02:03:55,640
But in actuality you were a member 
 of the Corleone crime organization?

2414
02:03:58,760 --> 02:04:02,320
We called it the Corleone family, 
 Senator. We called it the family.

2415
02:04:02,440 --> 02:04:04,720
What was your position?

2416
02:04:05,800 --> 02:04:08,560
At first, like everybody else, 
 I was a soldier.

2417
02:04:08,680 --> 02:04:11,960
- What is that? 
 - A button. You know, come on.

2418
02:04:12,040 --> 02:04:14,240
No, I don't know. Tell me.

2419
02:04:15,880 --> 02:04:19,840
When the boss says "push a button 
 on a guy," I push a button.

2420
02:04:19,960 --> 02:04:22,360
- See, Senator? 
 - Mr. Questadt.

2421
02:04:22,440 --> 02:04:25,240
- You mean you killed people? 
 - What?

2422
02:04:25,320 --> 02:04:30,080
You killed people 
 at the behest of your superiors?

2423
02:04:33,840 --> 02:04:35,040
Yeah, that's right, counselor.

2424
02:04:35,120 --> 02:04:40,520
And the head of your family 
 is Michael Corleone?

2425
02:04:40,640 --> 02:04:43,560
Yeah, counselor, Michael Corleone, 
 right.

2426
02:04:43,680 --> 02:04:46,920
Did you ever get such an order 
 directly from Michael Corleone?

2427
02:04:48,000 --> 02:04:50,080
No, I never talked to him.

2428
02:04:50,200 --> 02:04:53,840
Mr. Cicci, could you amplify 
 your answer a bit, please?

2429
02:04:53,960 --> 02:04:55,600
Do what?

2430
02:04:55,720 --> 02:04:59,840
Could you expand on your answer? 
 I'm interested in knowing...

2431
02:04:59,920 --> 02:05:02,200
was there always a buffer involved?

2432
02:05:03,080 --> 02:05:06,040
Someone in between you 
 and your possible superiors...

2433
02:05:06,120 --> 02:05:09,440
- who gave the actual orders? 
 - Yeah, right, a buffer.

2434
02:05:09,520 --> 02:05:12,560
The family had a lot of buffers.

2435
02:05:12,680 --> 02:05:14,640
Mr. Cicci, 
 you may find this very amusing...

2436
02:05:14,760 --> 02:05:17,600
but I promise you the members 
 of this committee do not.

2437
02:07:31,760 --> 02:07:34,960
If there's something I could do 
 for you, you come, we talk.

2438
02:12:47,120 --> 02:12:50,800
The rent stays like before.

2439
02:14:16,160 --> 02:14:20,880
Hey, what do you think? 
 God bless America. Big business.

2440
02:14:27,600 --> 02:14:30,880
- New York City. 
 - Would you mind speaking up?

2441
02:14:30,960 --> 02:14:32,840
New York City.

2442
02:14:32,920 --> 02:14:36,000
- Are you the son of Vito Corleone? 
 - Yes, I am.

2443
02:14:36,080 --> 02:14:39,960
- And where was he born? 
 - Corleone, Sicily.

2444
02:14:40,040 --> 02:14:42,160
Did he, at times, use an alias...

2445
02:14:42,280 --> 02:14:45,520
that was known in certain circles 
 as "Godfather"?

2446
02:14:46,400 --> 02:14:49,240
"Godfather" is a term 
 that was used by his friends...

2447
02:14:49,360 --> 02:14:53,080
one of affection, 
 one of respect.

2448
02:14:53,160 --> 02:14:57,440
Mr. Chairman, I would like 
 to verify the witness's statement.

2449
02:14:57,560 --> 02:15:00,000
For years now, a growing number 
 of my constituents...

2450
02:15:00,120 --> 02:15:02,560
have been of Italian descent...

2451
02:15:02,680 --> 02:15:04,560
and I've come to know them well.

2452
02:15:04,680 --> 02:15:09,600
They have honored me with their 
 support and with their friendship.

2453
02:15:09,720 --> 02:15:12,760
Indeed, I can proudly say 
 that some of my very best friends...

2454
02:15:12,840 --> 02:15:14,680
are Italian-Americans.

2455
02:15:15,640 --> 02:15:20,560
However, Mr. Chairman, at this time, 
 I have to leave these proceedings...

2456
02:15:20,680 --> 02:15:25,320
to preside over a very important 
 meeting of my own committee.

2457
02:15:25,440 --> 02:15:28,440
But before I leave, 
 I do want to say this--

2458
02:15:28,520 --> 02:15:32,880
that these hearings on the Mafia 
 are in no way whatsoever...

2459
02:15:33,000 --> 02:15:35,160
a slur upon 
 the great Italian people...

2460
02:15:35,240 --> 02:15:38,360
because I can state from 
 my own knowledge and experience...

2461
02:15:38,440 --> 02:15:41,960
that Italian-Americans are among 
 the most loyal...

2462
02:15:42,080 --> 02:15:44,280
most law-abiding, patriotic...

2463
02:15:44,360 --> 02:15:47,840
hard-working American citizens 
 in this land.

2464
02:15:47,960 --> 02:15:50,280
And it would be a shame, 
 Mr. Chairman...

2465
02:15:50,400 --> 02:15:52,480
if we allowed 
 a few rotten apples...

2466
02:15:52,560 --> 02:15:55,160
to give a bad name 
 to the whole barrel...

2467
02:15:55,240 --> 02:15:57,760
because from the time 
 of the great Christopher Columbus...

2468
02:15:57,840 --> 02:16:00,480
up to the time of Enrico Fermi...

2469
02:16:00,600 --> 02:16:02,520
right up until the present day...

2470
02:16:02,600 --> 02:16:04,440
Italian-Americans 
 have been pioneers...

2471
02:16:04,520 --> 02:16:06,640
in building and defending 
 our great nation.

2472
02:16:06,760 --> 02:16:08,880
They are the salt of the earth.

2473
02:16:09,000 --> 02:16:11,760
They are one of the backbones 
 of this country.

2474
02:16:15,760 --> 02:16:18,120
The chairman is calling 
 the meeting back to order.

2475
02:16:18,200 --> 02:16:21,680
I'm sure we all agree 
 with our esteemed colleague.

2476
02:16:21,800 --> 02:16:25,560
Now, Mr. Corleone, you have been 
 advised as to your legal rights.

2477
02:16:25,640 --> 02:16:29,160
We have testimony from a witness, 
 a previous witness...

2478
02:16:29,280 --> 02:16:31,680
one Willi Cicci.

2479
02:16:31,800 --> 02:16:33,640
He has stated that you are head...

2480
02:16:33,720 --> 02:16:35,920
of the most powerful Mafia family 
 in this country.

2481
02:16:36,040 --> 02:16:38,800
- Are you? 
 - No, I'm not.

2482
02:16:38,920 --> 02:16:42,240
The witness has testified that 
 you are personally responsible...

2483
02:16:42,360 --> 02:16:45,840
for the murder of a New York City 
 police captain in 1947.

2484
02:16:45,960 --> 02:16:49,520
And with him, 
 a man named Virgil Solozzo.

2485
02:16:49,640 --> 02:16:51,800
- Do you deny this? 
 - Yes, I do.

2486
02:16:51,880 --> 02:16:55,040
Is it true that in the year 1950...

2487
02:16:55,120 --> 02:16:59,320
you devised a murder of the heads 
 of the so-called "five families"...

2488
02:16:59,400 --> 02:17:01,600
in New York, to assume 
 and consolidate...

2489
02:17:01,720 --> 02:17:04,040
your nefarious power?

2490
02:17:04,120 --> 02:17:07,800
- That's a complete falsehood. 
 - Is it true...

2491
02:17:07,880 --> 02:17:11,600
you have a controlling interest 
 in three major hotels in Las Vegas?

2492
02:17:12,840 --> 02:17:16,320
No, it is not true. I own some stock 
 in some of the hotels there...

2493
02:17:16,400 --> 02:17:18,400
but very little.

2494
02:17:20,480 --> 02:17:24,400
I also have stock in IBM and IT&T.

2495
02:17:24,520 --> 02:17:29,640
Do you have any interests or control 
 over gambling and narcotics...

2496
02:17:29,760 --> 02:17:31,160
in the state of New York?

2497
02:17:31,240 --> 02:17:33,120
No, I do not.

2498
02:17:33,200 --> 02:17:36,240
Senator, my client would like to 
 read a statement for this committee.

2499
02:17:36,360 --> 02:17:40,000
Mr. Chairman, 
 I think this statement...

2500
02:17:40,080 --> 02:17:42,200
is totally out of order 
 at this time.

2501
02:17:42,280 --> 02:17:45,920
Sir, my client has answered every 
 question asked by this committee...

2502
02:17:46,040 --> 02:17:47,720
with the utmost sincerity.

2503
02:17:47,840 --> 02:17:50,640
He did not take the Fifth Amendment, 
 as it was his right to do...

2504
02:17:50,760 --> 02:17:53,280
so in all fairness I think 
 the statement should be heard.

2505
02:17:55,480 --> 02:17:58,520
No, I'm going to allow Mr. Corleone 
 to read his statement.

2506
02:17:58,600 --> 02:17:59,960
I'll put it in the record.

2507
02:18:01,880 --> 02:18:04,880
"In the hopes of clearing 
 my family name...

2508
02:18:05,000 --> 02:18:07,440
and my sincere desire to give 
 my children their fair share...

2509
02:18:07,560 --> 02:18:09,520
of the American way of life 
 without a blemish...

2510
02:18:09,640 --> 02:18:11,840
on their name and background...

2511
02:18:11,960 --> 02:18:13,920
I have appeared 
 before this committee...

2512
02:18:14,000 --> 02:18:16,800
and given it all the cooperation 
 in my power.

2513
02:18:18,120 --> 02:18:20,960
I consider it a great dishonor 
 to me personally...

2514
02:18:21,040 --> 02:18:23,360
to have to deny 
 that I am a criminal.

2515
02:18:24,240 --> 02:18:27,760
I wish to have the following 
 noted for the record:

2516
02:18:27,880 --> 02:18:31,720
that I served my country faithfully 
 and honorably in World War Two...

2517
02:18:31,840 --> 02:18:36,040
and was awarded a Navy Cross for 
 actions in defense of my country...

2518
02:18:37,560 --> 02:18:41,800
that I have never been arrested or 
 indicted for any crime whatsoever...

2519
02:18:41,880 --> 02:18:45,760
that no proof linking me to any 
 criminal conspiracy...

2520
02:18:45,880 --> 02:18:48,400
whether it is called "Mafia," 
 "Cosa Nostra"...

2521
02:18:48,520 --> 02:18:50,320
or whatever other name 
 you wish to give...

2522
02:18:50,440 --> 02:18:51,760
has ever been made public.

2523
02:18:53,000 --> 02:18:55,680
I have not taken refuge 
 behind the Fifth Amendment...

2524
02:18:55,800 --> 02:18:57,760
although it is my right to do so.

2525
02:19:00,680 --> 02:19:02,600
I challenge this committee...

2526
02:19:02,720 --> 02:19:06,040
to produce any witness 
 or evidence against me.

2527
02:19:06,120 --> 02:19:08,480
And if they do not...

2528
02:19:08,560 --> 02:19:11,880
I hope they will have the decency 
 to clear my name...

2529
02:19:12,000 --> 02:19:15,160
with the same publicity with which 
 they now have besmirched it."

2530
02:19:16,760 --> 02:19:19,640
I'm sure we're allquite impressed, 
 Mr. Corleone...

2531
02:19:19,760 --> 02:19:22,120
particularly with your love 
 for our country.

2532
02:19:22,240 --> 02:19:24,800
Committee will stand in recess 
 until 10:00 a. m. Monday morning...

2533
02:19:24,920 --> 02:19:26,760
at which time the committee 
 will produce a witness...

2534
02:19:26,840 --> 02:19:29,440
who will corroborate the charges 
 which were made against you today...

2535
02:19:29,560 --> 02:19:32,440
and at which time, Mr. Corleone, 
 you may very well be subject...

2536
02:19:32,520 --> 02:19:34,520
to indictment for perjury.

2537
02:19:34,600 --> 02:19:36,640
I remind you that 
 you're still under subpoena.

2538
02:19:36,760 --> 02:19:38,560
Adjourned.

2539
02:19:42,600 --> 02:19:45,280
Ten-to-one shot, you said.

2540
02:19:45,400 --> 02:19:48,240
Ten-to-one shot 
 he would take the Fifth...

2541
02:19:48,360 --> 02:19:50,000
and I lose.

2542
02:19:50,120 --> 02:19:52,000
You sound like my bookie.

2543
02:19:52,120 --> 02:19:54,080
I owe that monkey my life.

2544
02:19:55,840 --> 02:19:57,760
Well, just get 
 a good night's sleep.

2545
02:19:57,880 --> 02:20:01,120
- Good night's sleep. 
 - Got a big day tomorrow.

2546
02:20:01,240 --> 02:20:04,040
Got you a new suit, 
 a new shirt, new tie.

2547
02:20:05,600 --> 02:20:07,880
I'm gonna shave you myself 
 in the morning.

2548
02:20:08,800 --> 02:20:12,600
You're gonna look respectable for 
 50 million of your fellow Americans.

2549
02:20:13,960 --> 02:20:18,680
My life won't be worth a nickel 
 after tomorrow.

2550
02:20:18,760 --> 02:20:22,040
Come on. 
 I saw this thing 19 times.

2551
02:20:23,360 --> 02:20:25,760
You got a great home here, Frankie.

2552
02:20:25,880 --> 02:20:29,680
The rest of your life, nobody gets 
 near you, you're not going anywhere.

2553
02:20:29,800 --> 02:20:32,880
That's great. 
 Beautiful.

2554
02:20:33,000 --> 02:20:34,880
Some deal I made.

2555
02:20:34,960 --> 02:20:37,600
You'll live like a king. 
 You'll be a hero.

2556
02:20:37,720 --> 02:20:40,640
You'll live better in here 
 than most people on the outside.

2557
02:20:40,760 --> 02:20:43,440
Some deal. 
 Jesus.

2558
02:20:45,160 --> 02:20:48,880
Alive. 
 Pentangeli is alive.

2559
02:20:50,680 --> 02:20:55,600
- How'd they get their hands on him? 
 - Roth. He engineered it.

2560
02:20:56,360 --> 02:20:58,680
Frankie went to make a deal 
 with the Rosato brothers...

2561
02:20:58,760 --> 02:21:00,800
and they tried to kill him.

2562
02:21:00,880 --> 02:21:02,720
He thought you double-crossed him.

2563
02:21:04,280 --> 02:21:06,440
Our people with the New York 
 detective said he was halfdead...

2564
02:21:06,560 --> 02:21:10,080
scared stiffand calling out loud 
 that you turned on him.

2565
02:21:10,200 --> 02:21:12,800
They already had him on possession, 
 bookmaking, murder one...

2566
02:21:12,920 --> 02:21:14,720
and a lot more.

2567
02:21:16,200 --> 02:21:18,760
The FBI has him airtight.

2568
02:21:18,880 --> 02:21:21,600
He's on an army base, 
 24-hour guards.

2569
02:21:21,720 --> 02:21:23,840
No way we can get to him.

2570
02:21:23,920 --> 02:21:26,760
You've opened yourself 
 to five counts of perjury.

2571
02:21:28,880 --> 02:21:31,720
What about Fredo? 
 What does he know?

2572
02:21:31,800 --> 02:21:34,400
He says he doesn't know anything, 
 and I believe him.

2573
02:21:35,280 --> 02:21:39,040
Roth-- he played this one 
 beautifully.

2574
02:21:46,840 --> 02:21:48,680
I want to talk to Fredo.

2575
02:22:26,760 --> 02:22:28,600
I haven't got a lot to say, Mike.

2576
02:22:31,040 --> 02:22:33,400
We have time.

2577
02:22:33,520 --> 02:22:36,320
I was kept pretty much in the dark.

2578
02:22:37,920 --> 02:22:39,720
I didn't know all that much.

2579
02:22:40,960 --> 02:22:45,240
What about now? Is there anything 
 you can help me out with?

2580
02:22:46,040 --> 02:22:47,840
Anything you can tell me now?

2581
02:22:50,120 --> 02:22:52,400
They got Pentangeli, 
 that's all I can tell you.

2582
02:23:06,720 --> 02:23:10,080
I didn't know 
 it was gonna be a hit, Mike.

2583
02:23:10,200 --> 02:23:12,400
I swear to God, 
 I didn't know it was gonna be a hit.

2584
02:23:15,320 --> 02:23:19,560
Johnny Ola bumped into me 
 in Beverly Hills...

2585
02:23:21,200 --> 02:23:23,520
and he said 
 that he wanted to talk.

2586
02:23:25,720 --> 02:23:28,360
He said that you and Roth...

2587
02:23:28,480 --> 02:23:31,720
were in on a big deal together...

2588
02:23:34,000 --> 02:23:38,080
and that there was something in it 
 for me if I could help him out.

2589
02:23:38,160 --> 02:23:41,840
He said that you were being tough 
 on the negotiations.

2590
02:23:41,960 --> 02:23:46,160
But if they could get a little help 
 and close the deal fast...

2591
02:23:47,880 --> 02:23:50,000
it'd be good for the family.

2592
02:23:51,720 --> 02:23:53,680
You believed that story?

2593
02:23:53,800 --> 02:23:56,040
You believed that?

2594
02:23:56,160 --> 02:23:59,680
He said there was something in it 
 for me... on my own.

2595
02:23:59,760 --> 02:24:02,280
I've always taken care of you.

2596
02:24:02,400 --> 02:24:04,200
Taken care of me?

2597
02:24:05,280 --> 02:24:08,880
You're my kid brother. 
 You take care of me?

2598
02:24:09,000 --> 02:24:13,920
Did you ever think about that? 
 Did you ever once think about that?

2599
02:24:14,000 --> 02:24:17,280
Send Fredo off to do this, 
 send Fredo off to do that.

2600
02:24:18,640 --> 02:24:22,720
Let Fredo take care of some 
 Mickey Mouse nightclub somewhere.

2601
02:24:22,800 --> 02:24:25,600
Send Fredo to pick somebody up 
 at the airport.

2602
02:24:25,680 --> 02:24:28,840
I'm your older brother, Mike, 
 and I was stepped over!

2603
02:24:28,960 --> 02:24:33,520
- That's the way Pop wanted it. 
 - It ain't the way I wanted it!

2604
02:24:33,640 --> 02:24:36,000
I can handle things! 
 I'm smart!

2605
02:24:36,120 --> 02:24:39,920
Not like everybody says. 
 Like dumb. I'm smart...

2606
02:24:40,040 --> 02:24:42,000
and I want respect!

2607
02:24:49,600 --> 02:24:52,640
Is there anything you can tell me 
 about this investigation?

2608
02:24:52,720 --> 02:24:54,560
Anything more?

2609
02:25:02,280 --> 02:25:06,200
The Senate lawyer, Questadt...

2610
02:25:06,280 --> 02:25:07,800
he belongs to Roth.

2611
02:25:21,320 --> 02:25:23,320
You're nothing to me now.

2612
02:25:25,640 --> 02:25:27,760
You're not a brother, 
 you're not a friend.

2613
02:25:29,720 --> 02:25:32,400
I don't wanna know you 
 or what you do.

2614
02:25:33,520 --> 02:25:36,520
I don't wanna see you at the hotels.

2615
02:25:36,640 --> 02:25:38,920
I don't want you near my house.

2616
02:25:41,000 --> 02:25:43,720
When you see our mother, 
 I wanna know a day in advance...

2617
02:25:43,840 --> 02:25:45,240
so I won't be there.

2618
02:25:47,080 --> 02:25:49,720
You understand?

2619
02:26:06,120 --> 02:26:09,800
I don't want anything to happen 
 to him while my mother's alive.

2620
02:26:57,680 --> 02:27:01,160
There are more people 
 than a ball game in here.

2621
02:27:01,280 --> 02:27:03,080
There's Willi Cicci.

2622
02:27:24,240 --> 02:27:26,080
This committee will come to order.

2623
02:27:28,960 --> 02:27:31,520
- State your name, please. 
 - Frank Pentangeli.

2624
02:27:31,600 --> 02:27:35,160
- And where were you born? 
 - Partanego. Outside of Palermo.

2625
02:27:35,240 --> 02:27:37,400
Where do you live now?

2626
02:27:37,480 --> 02:27:41,720
I live in an army barracks 
 with the FBI guys.

2627
02:27:42,760 --> 02:27:47,720
We have here, finally, a witness 
 that will further testify...

2628
02:27:47,840 --> 02:27:50,400
to Michael Corleone's rule 
 over a criminal empire...

2629
02:27:50,520 --> 02:27:52,440
that controls all of the gambling 
 in this country...

2630
02:27:52,560 --> 02:27:53,920
and perhaps in other countries.

2631
02:27:54,000 --> 02:27:59,040
This witness had no buffer between 
 himself and Michael Corleone.

2632
02:27:59,160 --> 02:28:02,560
He can corroborate ourcharges on 
 enough counts for this committee...

2633
02:28:02,680 --> 02:28:06,880
to recommend a charge of perjury 
 against Michael Corleone.

2634
02:28:06,960 --> 02:28:08,600
- Senator. 
 - Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

2635
02:28:10,040 --> 02:28:11,200
Mr. Pentangeli.

2636
02:28:15,240 --> 02:28:18,240
Were you a member 
 of the Corleone family?

2637
02:28:18,360 --> 02:28:22,720
Did you serve under 
 caporegime Peter Clemenza...

2638
02:28:22,840 --> 02:28:27,320
under Vito Corleone, 
 also known as the "Godfather"?

2639
02:28:33,400 --> 02:28:35,440
I never knew no Godfather.

2640
02:28:38,120 --> 02:28:39,920
I have my own family, Senator.

2641
02:28:43,720 --> 02:28:47,840
Mr. Pentangeli, you are 
 contradicting a sworn statement...

2642
02:28:47,920 --> 02:28:49,760
you'd previously made to me 
 and signed.

2643
02:28:49,840 --> 02:28:53,280
I ask you again, sir, 
 here and now under oath...

2644
02:28:53,360 --> 02:28:57,720
were you at anytime 
 a memberof a crime organization...

2645
02:28:57,800 --> 02:28:59,160
headed by Michael Corleone?

2646
02:28:59,240 --> 02:29:02,800
I don't know nothing about that.

2647
02:29:05,760 --> 02:29:09,520
I was in the olive oil business 
 with his father...

2648
02:29:09,640 --> 02:29:11,920
but that was a long time ago, 
 that's all.

2649
02:29:13,000 --> 02:29:14,840
We have a sworn affidavit.

2650
02:29:16,280 --> 02:29:19,240
We have it-- 
 your sworn affidavit...

2651
02:29:19,360 --> 02:29:21,720
that you murdered on 
 the orders of Michael Corleone.

2652
02:29:21,840 --> 02:29:23,920
Do you deny that confession?

2653
02:29:24,040 --> 02:29:26,680
And do you realize what will happen 
 as a result of your denial?

2654
02:29:26,760 --> 02:29:29,760
Look, the FBI guys, 
 they promised me a deal...

2655
02:29:29,880 --> 02:29:33,440
so I made up a lot of stuff 
 about Michael Corleone...

2656
02:29:33,560 --> 02:29:35,440
'cause that's what they wanted.

2657
02:29:35,560 --> 02:29:39,200
But it was all lies-- 
 everything.

2658
02:29:40,120 --> 02:29:42,400
And they kept saying...

2659
02:29:42,480 --> 02:29:44,560
Michael Corleone did this...

2660
02:29:44,680 --> 02:29:47,120
and that Michael Corleone did that.

2661
02:29:48,520 --> 02:29:52,440
So I said,"Yeah, sure!"

2662
02:29:52,520 --> 02:29:56,000
Mr. Corleone, would you kindly 
 identify for the committee...

2663
02:29:56,080 --> 02:29:57,920
the gentleman sitting 
 to your left?

2664
02:29:58,000 --> 02:29:59,840
I can answer that.

2665
02:30:01,080 --> 02:30:03,960
His name is Vincenzo Pentangeli.

2666
02:30:04,040 --> 02:30:08,000
- Is he related to the witness? 
 - He is, I believe, his brother.

2667
02:30:08,080 --> 02:30:10,480
Will he come forward 
 and be sworn, sir?

2668
02:30:10,600 --> 02:30:13,160
Sir, this man 
 does not understand English.

2669
02:30:13,280 --> 02:30:16,760
He came at his own expense to aid 
 his brother in this time of trouble.

2670
02:30:16,840 --> 02:30:20,360
He's not under subpoena. 
 His reputation is impeccable.

2671
02:30:20,480 --> 02:30:22,240
Are you saying he knows nothing 
 about these matters?

2672
02:30:22,360 --> 02:30:23,680
To my knowledge, nothing.

2673
02:30:23,800 --> 02:30:26,640
I'm gonna find out 
 what the hell happened here.

2674
02:30:26,760 --> 02:30:28,640
Allright, this committee 
 is now adjourned.

2675
02:30:28,760 --> 02:30:30,880
- The witness is excused. 
 - Senator!

2676
02:30:33,160 --> 02:30:35,840
This committee owes an apology!

2677
02:30:35,960 --> 02:30:39,680
This committee owes an apology. 
 Apology, Senator.

2678
02:31:06,440 --> 02:31:09,920
- Michael, excuse me. 
 - Hold on a minute.

2679
02:31:10,000 --> 02:31:12,600
The children are outside. 
 We're going.

2680
02:31:15,320 --> 02:31:17,520
What do you mean you're going? 
 We're all gonna leave tomorrow.

2681
02:31:21,960 --> 02:31:23,760
I'll be in my room.

2682
02:31:27,040 --> 02:31:29,880
Michael, I'm not going 
 back to Nevada.

2683
02:31:29,960 --> 02:31:32,760
I brought the children 
 to say good-bye to you.

2684
02:31:36,480 --> 02:31:38,520
I want you to know 
 I'm very happy for you.

2685
02:31:38,600 --> 02:31:41,040
I suppose I always knew 
 you were too smart...

2686
02:31:41,160 --> 02:31:43,000
to let any of them 
 ever beat you.

2687
02:31:44,800 --> 02:31:49,080
- Why don't you sit down? 
 - I'm not going to stay long.

2688
02:31:49,160 --> 02:31:51,480
There are some things 
 I'd like to talk to you about.

2689
02:31:53,160 --> 02:31:55,480
Some things that have been 
 on my mind.

2690
02:31:56,680 --> 02:32:00,640
- Changes I wanna make. 
 - I think it's too late for changes.

2691
02:32:02,080 --> 02:32:04,080
I promised myself 
 I wasn't going to say anything.

2692
02:32:04,200 --> 02:32:07,480
You're too late.

2693
02:32:11,720 --> 02:32:14,000
What really happened 
 with Pentangeli?

2694
02:32:20,040 --> 02:32:21,960
His brother came, helped him.

2695
02:32:22,080 --> 02:32:24,880
I didn't even know 
 he had a brother.

2696
02:32:25,000 --> 02:32:26,800
Where is he now?

2697
02:32:27,960 --> 02:32:30,280
He's on a plane back to Sicily.

2698
02:32:31,040 --> 02:32:33,360
All he had to do 
 was show his face.

2699
02:32:35,240 --> 02:32:39,600
It was between the brothers. 
 I had nothing to do with it.

2700
02:32:47,440 --> 02:32:52,320
Nobody is going-- 
 not you, not the kids! You hear me?

2701
02:32:52,440 --> 02:32:56,000
You're my wife, they're my children. 
 I love you. I won't allow it.

2702
02:32:57,040 --> 02:33:00,760
You say you love me, then you 
 talk about allowing me to leave!

2703
02:33:00,840 --> 02:33:03,800
Things have been going on for years 
 between men and women...

2704
02:33:03,880 --> 02:33:05,720
- that will not change. 
 - You've become blind!

2705
02:33:05,800 --> 02:33:08,600
- Blind to what? 
 - Look what happened to us.

2706
02:33:08,680 --> 02:33:11,640
- Look what's happened to our son! 
 - Nothing's happened--

2707
02:33:11,720 --> 02:33:14,760
- Anthony is fine! 
 - Anthony is not fine!

2708
02:33:14,880 --> 02:33:16,720
- I don't wanna hear about it! 
 - You will!

2709
02:33:16,840 --> 02:33:19,240
Anthony's not fine!

2710
02:33:19,360 --> 02:33:20,920
I don't wanna hear about it!

2711
02:33:21,800 --> 02:33:23,280
Over!

2712
02:33:35,880 --> 02:33:38,640
At this moment, 
 I feel no love for you at all.

2713
02:33:40,240 --> 02:33:42,560
I never thought 
 that would ever happen...

2714
02:33:43,760 --> 02:33:45,240
but it has.

2715
02:34:03,640 --> 02:34:05,240
We're gonna leave tomorrow.

2716
02:34:06,280 --> 02:34:09,120
Okay? Why don't you take the kids 
 back to their room?

2717
02:34:09,200 --> 02:34:11,040
You haven't heard me.

2718
02:34:12,520 --> 02:34:15,160
What do you want from me?

2719
02:34:15,240 --> 02:34:17,240
Do you expect me to let you go?

2720
02:34:17,360 --> 02:34:21,000
Do you expect me to let you take 
 my children from me?

2721
02:34:22,080 --> 02:34:24,960
Don't you know me? Don't you know 
 that that's an impossibility?

2722
02:34:25,080 --> 02:34:27,000
That that could never happen?

2723
02:34:27,120 --> 02:34:30,960
That I'd use all my power to keep 
 something like that from happening?

2724
02:34:31,880 --> 02:34:34,040
Don't you know that?

2725
02:34:40,560 --> 02:34:43,280
Now, in time...

2726
02:34:43,400 --> 02:34:44,800
you'll feel differently.

2727
02:34:46,440 --> 02:34:48,960
You'll be glad I stopped you now.

2728
02:34:51,040 --> 02:34:52,920
I know that.

2729
02:34:55,000 --> 02:34:57,760
I know you blame me 
 for losing the baby.

2730
02:34:59,880 --> 02:35:01,920
Yes.

2731
02:35:02,040 --> 02:35:04,320
I know what that meant to you.

2732
02:35:06,800 --> 02:35:09,600
I'll make it up to you.

2733
02:35:09,720 --> 02:35:11,520
I swear, I'll make it up to you.

2734
02:35:13,640 --> 02:35:15,480
I'm gonna change.

2735
02:35:16,680 --> 02:35:18,320
I'll change.

2736
02:35:18,440 --> 02:35:20,800
I've learned that I have 
 the strength to change.

2737
02:35:23,080 --> 02:35:25,360
And you'll forget about 
 this miscarriage...

2738
02:35:26,760 --> 02:35:28,240
and we'll have another child...

2739
02:35:28,360 --> 02:35:31,040
and we'll go on-- 
 you and I.

2740
02:35:32,520 --> 02:35:34,360
We'll go on.

2741
02:35:37,880 --> 02:35:39,840
You are blind.

2742
02:35:41,480 --> 02:35:43,800
It wasn't a miscarriage.

2743
02:35:45,760 --> 02:35:47,240
It was an abortion.

2744
02:35:48,960 --> 02:35:50,760
An abortion.

2745
02:35:51,640 --> 02:35:54,000
Just like our marriage 
 is an abortion.

2746
02:35:54,920 --> 02:35:57,920
Something that's unholy and evil.

2747
02:35:59,680 --> 02:36:02,680
I didn't want your son!

2748
02:36:02,760 --> 02:36:06,960
I wouldn't bring another one 
 of your sons into this world!

2749
02:36:08,280 --> 02:36:10,640
It was an abortion!

2750
02:36:10,760 --> 02:36:13,440
It was a son! A son! 
 And I had it killed...

2751
02:36:13,560 --> 02:36:16,240
because this must all end!

2752
02:36:17,800 --> 02:36:21,680
I know now that it's over. 
 I knew it then.

2753
02:36:22,920 --> 02:36:25,200
There would be no way...

2754
02:36:25,320 --> 02:36:28,160
no way you could ever forgive me...

2755
02:36:28,240 --> 02:36:30,520
not with this Sicilian thing...

2756
02:36:30,600 --> 02:36:32,760
that's been going on 
 for 2,000 years--

2757
02:36:32,840 --> 02:36:34,680
Bitch!

2758
02:36:40,160 --> 02:36:43,280
- You won't take my children. 
 - I will.

2759
02:36:43,400 --> 02:36:47,120
- You won't take my children! 
 - They're my children too.

2760
02:38:13,480 --> 02:38:16,760
Fredo, here's this for Grandma.

2761
02:38:26,000 --> 02:38:27,200
What are you doing?

2762
02:43:25,160 --> 02:43:26,960
Michael, say good-bye.

2763
02:44:41,320 --> 02:44:43,280
Can I speak with you 
 for a second?

2764
02:44:51,720 --> 02:44:55,640
- Where's Mike? 
 - Waiting foryou to leave.

2765
02:44:59,080 --> 02:45:00,920
Can I talk with him?

2766
02:45:01,000 --> 02:45:02,840
Sorry, no chance.

2767
02:45:03,760 --> 02:45:06,560
- Can I see him? 
 - He's in the boathouse.

2768
02:45:19,640 --> 02:45:21,440
Michael, it's Connie.

2769
02:45:46,640 --> 02:45:49,120
I'd like to stay close to home now, 
 if it's all right.

2770
02:45:58,040 --> 02:45:59,960
Is Kay coming?

2771
02:46:12,040 --> 02:46:14,880
Fredo's in the house with Mama.

2772
02:46:14,960 --> 02:46:18,720
He asked for you, 
 and Tom said you wouldn't see him.

2773
02:46:21,960 --> 02:46:23,800
That's right.

2774
02:46:26,280 --> 02:46:29,520
Kids, why don't you go outside 
 for a while?

2775
02:46:33,640 --> 02:46:35,640
Please, I wanna talk to you.

2776
02:46:47,040 --> 02:46:50,360
I hated you for so many years.

2777
02:46:50,440 --> 02:46:54,320
I think that I did things to myself, 
 to hurt myself...

2778
02:46:54,440 --> 02:46:56,240
so that you'd know...

2779
02:46:59,200 --> 02:47:01,000
that I could hurt you.

2780
02:47:07,160 --> 02:47:11,080
You were just being strong 
 for all of us the way Papa was.

2781
02:47:12,000 --> 02:47:13,800
And I forgive you.

2782
02:47:18,000 --> 02:47:20,840
Can't you forgive Fredo?

2783
02:47:20,960 --> 02:47:25,640
He's so sweet 
 and helpless without you.

2784
02:47:31,560 --> 02:47:34,960
You need me. 
 I want to take care ofyou now.

2785
02:49:25,640 --> 02:49:27,000
Sit down.

2786
02:49:37,920 --> 02:49:40,960
Our friend and business partner, 
 Hyman Roth, is in the news.

2787
02:49:42,760 --> 02:49:44,840
You hear about it?

2788
02:49:44,960 --> 02:49:46,760
I hear that he's in Israel.

2789
02:49:47,840 --> 02:49:50,120
And the High Court in Israel 
 turned down his request...

2790
02:49:50,240 --> 02:49:52,320
to live there as a returned Jew.

2791
02:49:52,440 --> 02:49:56,240
His passport's been invalidated, 
 except for return to the US.

2792
02:49:56,360 --> 02:49:58,720
He landed in Buenos Aires yesterday.

2793
02:49:58,840 --> 02:50:01,680
He offered a gift of a million 
 dollars if they let him live there.

2794
02:50:03,560 --> 02:50:05,360
They turned him down.

2795
02:50:05,480 --> 02:50:09,560
- He's gonna try Panama. 
 - Panama won't take him.

2796
02:50:09,640 --> 02:50:12,040
Not for a million, 
 not for ten million.

2797
02:50:12,160 --> 02:50:13,960
His medical condition 
 is reported as terminal.

2798
02:50:14,080 --> 02:50:16,880
He's only gonna live 
 another six months anyway.

2799
02:50:17,000 --> 02:50:19,920
He's been dying of 
 the same heart attack for 20 years.

2800
02:50:20,040 --> 02:50:24,960
- That plane goes to Miami. 
 - Right. That's where I want it met.

2801
02:50:25,080 --> 02:50:28,160
Mike, that's impossible. 
 They'll turn him over directly...

2802
02:50:28,240 --> 02:50:30,360
to the Internal Revenue, Customs 
 and half the FBl.

2803
02:50:30,440 --> 02:50:33,560
It's not impossible. 
 Nothing's impossible.

2804
02:50:33,640 --> 02:50:35,920
It would be like trying to kill 
 the president. No way to get to him.

2805
02:50:37,200 --> 02:50:39,040
You know, you surprise me.

2806
02:50:42,120 --> 02:50:45,600
If anything in this life 
 is certain--

2807
02:50:45,720 --> 02:50:47,880
if history's taught us anything...

2808
02:50:48,760 --> 02:50:51,280
it's that you can kill anyone.

2809
02:50:58,320 --> 02:51:01,240
Difficult, not impossible.

2810
02:51:01,320 --> 02:51:03,520
Good.

2811
02:51:05,640 --> 02:51:08,760
Why did you ask me if something 
 was wrong when I came in?

2812
02:51:12,200 --> 02:51:16,040
I thought you were 
 gonna tell me that...

2813
02:51:16,160 --> 02:51:17,960
you were moving 
 your family to Vegas.

2814
02:51:19,680 --> 02:51:25,080
And that you'd been offered the 
 vice presidency of the hotels there.

2815
02:51:25,160 --> 02:51:27,120
- I thought you'd tell me that. 
 - I turned them down.

2816
02:51:27,240 --> 02:51:28,880
Do I have to tell you 
 about every offer that I turn down?

2817
02:51:33,880 --> 02:51:34,960
Let's do business.

2818
02:51:35,080 --> 02:51:37,360
All right.

2819
02:51:38,360 --> 02:51:40,320
Just consider this. 
 Just consider it.

2820
02:51:42,320 --> 02:51:43,920
Now, Roth and the Rosatos 
 are on the run.

2821
02:51:44,040 --> 02:51:46,880
Are they worth it, 
 and are they strong enough?

2822
02:51:46,960 --> 02:51:50,640
Is it worth it? 
 I mean, you won.

2823
02:51:50,760 --> 02:51:52,560
Do you want to wipe 
 everybody out?

2824
02:51:52,680 --> 02:51:55,520
I don't feel I have to wipe 
 everybody out--

2825
02:51:55,600 --> 02:51:58,600
just my enemies, that's all.

2826
02:52:04,600 --> 02:52:07,200
You gonna come along with me on 
 these things I have to do or what?

2827
02:52:09,520 --> 02:52:13,840
'Cause if not, you can take your 
 wife, family and your mistress...

2828
02:52:13,920 --> 02:52:16,240
move them all to Las Vegas.

2829
02:52:20,720 --> 02:52:25,360
Why do you hurt me? I've always been 
 loyal to you. I mean, what is this?

2830
02:52:38,560 --> 02:52:40,400
What is it that you want me to do?

2831
02:52:43,600 --> 02:52:47,480
How would you like it if I taught 
 you how to catch really big fish?

2832
02:52:47,600 --> 02:52:50,280
- Would you like that? 
 - Okay.

2833
02:52:50,400 --> 02:52:53,120
You know, when I was your age...

2834
02:52:53,240 --> 02:52:56,480
I went out fishing 
 with all my brothers...

2835
02:52:56,600 --> 02:52:58,880
and my father...

2836
02:52:59,000 --> 02:53:00,920
everybody...

2837
02:53:01,040 --> 02:53:03,840
and I was the only one 
 that caught a fish.

2838
02:53:05,240 --> 02:53:07,520
Nobody else could catch one, 
 except me.

2839
02:53:07,600 --> 02:53:09,440
You know how I did it?

